  "description": "A fairly advanced two-chamber inverter refrigerator, presented on the market as part of the mid-level iQ300 family from the popular Siemens brand. Among the main advantages of the model, first of all, it is worth highlighting a reliable inverter compressor, two cooling circuits (for the refrigerator and separately for the freezer), full support for Full No Frost technology, as well as advanced equipment. The total useful volume of the Siemens KG39NVL316 refrigerator is 366 liters, while the model is dressed in a case measuring 203x60x66 cm. Let's start with the refrigerator compartment, whose capacity is 255 liters. Inside, there is a special zero chamber for 24 liters, a MultiAirflow dynamic cooling system for the most even distribution of cold air, and an Airfresh deodorizing filter to eliminate unpleasant or simply pungent odors. There is also the SuperCooling function, which enables the temperature in the refrigerator compartment to drop quickly to +2°C. The freezer of this model is located below and is capable of freezing up to 14 kg of food per day, and the lowest maintained temperature inside is -24 ° C.",
